#Approach:

Largest Odd Number in String – Right to Left Traversal Approach

Is problem me hume given string me sabse bada odd-valued substring find karna hai.
Kyunki hume largest value chahiye, isliye hume number ka maximum possible prefix lena chahiye.

Ek number tabhi odd hota hai jab uska last digit odd ho
(1, 3, 5, 7, 9).

Isliye hum string ko right se left traverse karte hain
aur pehla aisa digit dhoondte hain jo odd ho.

Jaise hi odd digit mil jaye,
to starting index 0 se us index tak ka substring return kar dete hain.
Ye hi largest possible odd substring hoga,
kyunki hum maximum length ka prefix le rahe hote hain.

Agar poori string me koi bhi odd digit na mile,
to empty string return kar dete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1) (excluding output substring)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public String largestOddNumber(String num) {
        int n = num.length();
        
        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            char ch = num.charAt(i);
            int digit = ch - '0';
            //Meaning it is an odd number
            if(digit % 2 == 1){
                return num.substring(0, i+1);
            }
        }
        return "";
        
    }
}
